description: '''Freakbeat''' is a loosely defined [[subgenre]] of [[rock music]] developed mainly by harder-driving British [[Mod (subculture)|mod]] groups during the [[British Invasion]] and [[Swinging London]] period of the mid-to late 1960s. The genre bridges [[British R&B|R&B]], [[Beat music|beat]] and early [[Psychedelic rock|psychedelia]].
top_artists: Dave Dee, Dozy, Beaky, Mick & Tich
